{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"RemotePlayback.watchAvailability()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RemotePlayback/watchAvailability","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>watchAvailability()</code></strong> method of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RemotePlayback\"><code>RemotePlayback</code></a> interface watches the list of available remote playback devices and returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that resolves with the <code>callbackId</code> of a remote playback device.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">watchAvailability(RemotePlaybackAvailabilityCallback)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"remoteplaybackavailabilitycallbackboolean\"><code>RemotePlaybackAvailabilityCallback(boolean)</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A callback that allows the page to obtain the remote playback device availability for the corresponding media element. It is passed a boolean which, if true, indicates that remote playback is available.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that resolves with an integer. This is the <code>callbackId</code> for the identified remote playback device.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"exceptions","title":"Exceptions","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"invalidstateerror\"><code>InvalidStateError</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Thrown if <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLMediaElement/disableRemotePlayback\" title=\"disableRemotePlayback\"><code>disableRemotePlayback</code></a> is <code>true</code> for the media element.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"notsupportederror\"><code>NotSupportedError</code> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Thrown if the user agent is unable to continuously monitor the list of available remote playback devices.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>In the following example, after checking that there is no currently connected device, <code>watchAvailability()</code> is used to watch for remote devices becoming available. <a href=\"https://beaufortfrancois.github.io/sandbox/media/remote-playback.html\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">See the working example</a> (Requires a supported device and a connected remote playback device).</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code> <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>video<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>remote<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>state <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token string\">'disconnected'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  video<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>remote<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">watchAvailability</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>handleAvailabilityChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">id</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">&gt; Started watching remote device availability: </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>id<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    callbackId <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> id\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/remote-playback/#dom-remoteplayback-watchavailability","title":"Remote Playback API"}],"query":"api.RemotePlayback.watchAvailability"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.RemotePlayback.watchAvailability","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RemotePlayback/watchAvailability/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The watchAvailability() method of the RemotePlayback interface watches the list of available remote playback devices and returns a Promise that resolves with the callbackId of a remote playback device.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T06:09:49.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/remoteplayback/watchavailability","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/remoteplayback/watchavailability/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/2b8f5d9a29f00aea5d2edfa78d1fb90c51752858","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RemotePlayback","title":"RemotePlayback"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RemotePlayback/watchAvailability","title":"RemotePlayback.watchAvailability()"}],"pageTitle":"RemotePlayback.watchAvailability() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}